WHAT does Madonna, Sarah Miles and Juan Manuel Márquez all have in common? They drink and consume their own urine. While that may be tough to swallow, drinking urine is not as weird as it sounds. According to health experts and historians, the ancient Indian health system of Ayurveda used the consumption of urine to treat conditions such as asthma, allergies, indigestion, wrinkles and even cancer. Similarly, the China Urine Therapy Association claimed that drinking and bathing in urine could cure constipation and skin scores. Recent mixologists have also discovered that one can make cocktails with urine. According to Plumbworld, there are several types of cocktails with a dash of pee, namely: 1. The urinegasm If you’re a fan of rich, Baileys-based cocktails, then this is the perfect drink for you. It includes almond extract, coffee syrup, Baileys Irish cream, ice and fresh urine. 2. Golden shower Meet the ideal option if you’re looking for a liqueur and urine-based cocktail. The golden shower ingredients include orange juice, apple juice, Galliano, some ice and urine. 3. Yellow Russian This was taken from The Dude, the main character in the film The Big Lebowski, who is known for near-continual consumption of white Russian cocktails. The yellow Russian is smooth and creamy with a refreshing tang of urine. Its main ingredients include coffee syrup, cream, chocolate powder, coffee bean, some ice and fresh urine. 4. Pee and tonic For a lower-calorie option, try this drink. As with gin, the amount of pee you add depends on your personal taste. Just add tonic water and fresh pee, and you’re good to go. 5. Buck’s piss Ideal for weddings, buck’s piss makes for a perfect celebration drink because of its fruitiness and added tang of urine. This daytime drink includes champagne, orange juice and fresh urine. It also makes the ideal toast drink!